# Python – Data Analysis Projects

## Project Overview

This folder contains my data analysis projects built in Python, focusing on extracting meaningful business insights from raw transactional and structured datasets.

Each project follows an end-to-end analytical workflow, from data cleaning and exploration to visualization and interpretation.

---

## Goals of This Project

- Practice real-world data analysis using Python
- Strengthen analytical thinking and problem-solving
- Build a strong portfolio for data analyst / business analyst roles
- Translate raw data into clear, business-focused insights

---

## Skills Covered

Across the projects in this folder, I focus on developing:

- Data cleaning and preprocessing
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Aggregation and grouping (groupby)
- Data visualization (matplotlib, seaborn)
- Trend and revenue analysis
- Customer segmentation (e.g. RFM)
- Cohort and retention analysis
- Business insight generation

---

## Tools Used

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Jupyter Notebook

---

## Structure

Each project folder contains:

- a Jupyter Notebook (.ipynb) with the full analysis
- step-by-step explanations and visualizations
- final conclusions and business recommendations

---

## Projects

- Online Retail Analysis
  Customer, product, and revenue analysis including RFM segmentation and cohort-based retention insights.
